            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1592249548828-finding-the-right-candidate--interviews" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1592249548828-finding-the-right-candidate--interviews" aria-controls="accordion-content-1592249548828-finding-the-right-candidate--interviews" aria-expanded="false">
                            Finding the right candidate: Interviews
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1592249548828-finding-the-right-candidate--interviews" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1592249548828-finding-the-right-candidate--interviews">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1592249548828 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resTable parbase section">























 



	<div class="scrollIndicator hidden">
		<i class="fa fa-long-arrow-left" aria-hidden="true"></i> Swipe to see more <i class="fa fa-long-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
	</div>
	<div id="e15c063e-3d39-4017-b331-dc74e1363fcd">
		<table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1" border="0">
<tbody><tr><th width="50%" height="50" scope="col" style="text-align: left;">What can you do?</th>
<th width="50%" height="50" scope="col" style="text-align: left;">Why?</th>
</tr><tr><td>Ask questions about how their identity and/or experiences inform their teaching and research.</td>
<td>This demonstrates Ryerson’s commitment to equity, diversity and inclusion in all aspects of university life. It can make candidates feel as though their knowledges, perspectives and lived experiences will be valued at the university.</td>
</tr><tr><td>Develop questions based on selection criteria, including EDI criteria, included in the posting. Use OVPECI suggested interview questions. </td>
<td>These questions will help you understand how the candidate’s diverse perspectives, knowledges and experience can add value to the department/school.</td>
</tr></tbody></table>

	</div>




	<script>
	
	//convert to plugin in pure js....later (soon)
	$(document).ready(function() {
		$('#e15c063e-3d39-4017-b331-dc74e1363fcd table').addClass("table");
	    
		$('#e15c063e-3d39-4017-b331-dc74e1363fcd table').addClass("table-bordered");
		
	    
	} );
	</script>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#e15c063e-3d39-4017-b331-dc74e1363fcd");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="36cb66bb-ed6d-45a3-8aee-b7d4317bc630" >

    <h3><a id="ovpeci-suggested-interview-questions"></a>Suggested interview questions from the OVPECI</h3> 
<h4>Equity, diversity and inclusion-related questions</h4> 
<ol> 
 <li>Ryerson is highly committed to equity, diversity and inclusion in all of our activities on campus. Equity, Diversity and Inclusion are also the core values of Ryerson’s Academic Plan. What specific strategies have you used to infuse equity, diversity and inclusion into your work?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Describe how you have created research and creative opportunities (graduate students, postdoctoral fellows, research associates, research assistants, etc.) for people from under-represented groups, including women, Indigenous Peoples, persons with disabilities, racialized people and people of all sexual orientations and gender identities and expressions?&nbsp;</li> 
</ol> 
<h4>Research/creative activities&nbsp;</h4> 
<ol> 
 <li>Could you comment on your research or creative collaborations? How do you plan to collaborate while at Ryerson? What role has diversity played in your research or creative collaborations?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Describe any ties that your research or creative activities have or may have with industry and/or community partners.</li> 
 <li>Describe how you have organized and implemented your research or creative activity projects. How would you hire and supervise people to create a team that would bring diverse perspectives and experiences to the work. How would you include representation from under represented equity seeking groups and foster a culture of respect, equity and inclusion?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>What strategies do you use to effectively balance a busy teaching, research and service load, and how do you build in time to stay current?</li> 
</ol> 
<h4>Teaching&nbsp;</h4> 
<ol> 
 <li>What experience do you have teaching undergraduate and graduate courses? What courses would you like to teach at Ryerson? What experience do you have teaching students with diverse backgrounds, experiences and worldviews?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Describe your most difficult teaching experience. What happened? What was the impact of your actions on you and the students?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>What experience do you have teaching students with diverse backgrounds, experiences and worldviews?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>What is your experience in developing new programs and/or new courses? What obstacles did you overcome? What were the results?&nbsp;</li> 
</ol> 
<h4>Service&nbsp;</h4> 
<ol> 
 <li>What have you done recently, outside of research and &nbsp; teaching, to contribute to your profession (organizing conferences, etc.)? What have you done recently, outside of research and teaching, to contribute to the community, both inside and outside of the university?&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>If hired, then what service contributions can you make to the Department and to Ryerson?</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#36cb66bb-ed6d-45a3-8aee-b7d4317bc630");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="73353ff6-b70a-4c33-8386-daa222e994cd" >

    
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#73353ff6-b70a-4c33-8386-daa222e994cd");});</script></div>

